  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I love the idea, but wondering about retro-compatibility. Adding the count in the default template of the header might break a lot of designs. And it makes much more sense for UI where the list is hidden, not so much when it is displayed.\n- Adding a data-attribute should be trivial\n- Adding an `__active` class on the header if a filter is selected should be doable as well\n- Instead of changing the default template, I would simply pass the count to the template, and let users use this information or not in their design.\n\nWDYT?\n",
