    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> If you have the correct attribute on an element, you can easily add the count through CSS with\n\nI understand but at the same time this would be the first time we include data this way, I would first just pass the data in the template and build the same without the need to have another data attribute.\n\nEvery css class or data attribute we add widen the surface of the API (and raise the complexity). If it's doable without it then we should not add the data attribute.\n",
